Angular - Front-end

1. ng new project_name - create a project

2. ng serve --open - run in browser
 
3. ng g c component_name - create a component

4. ng g s service-name - create a service


Basic Concepts

1. Module - To import libraries , Root module - AppModule

2. Components - To generate ts,html,css, Root-component -  AppComponent

3. Data Binding - Sharing data within a component

    3.1 One Way Binding - Only single directional sharing 

        3.1.1 Component (ts file) to view (html file)
         
            3.1.1.1    String Interpolation   -  {{Variable name}}   

            3.1.1.2    Property Binding       - [tag-attribute] = ""class-property"
        
        3.1.2 View (html file) to component (ts file)

            3.1.2.1 Event Binding - (event-name)=""function-call"

            3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event- (event-name)=""function-call($event)"
            
            3.1.2.3 Template referancing Variable: syntax:#variable-name

     3.2 Two way Binding - same time data sharing in both direction

        3.2.1 FormsModule - Import in AppModule

            ngModel - syntax: [(ngModel)]="variable-name" , set name attribute if it is inside form tag


4. Component Path set up

5. Dependency Injection - inside constructor of a class

6. Angular Services

7. ngSubmit

8. Angular Form

    8.1 Template Driven Form

    8.2 Modern Driven Form - ReactiveForms - Import ReactiveFormsModule
        (form group, form array, form control)

9.Angular Directives - DOM Manipulation

    9.1 Component Directives

    9.2 Structural Directive - prefix

    


